billionaire views us as interchangeable economic units.\n\nOhio, REJECT VIVEK.\n\nSave Ohio, Vote Putsch. May 5", "last_comment_created": 1773798313055, "content": "", "score_down": 3, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 26, "score_up": 122, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"twitter": {"quotedTweet": false, "images": false, "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 1, "created": 1773761404000, "id": "2033928864351576338", "video": {"preview": "https://pbs.twimg.com/amplify_video_thumb/2033928805710995456/img/98oVKTjxHRcw_Vdg.jpg", "mpeg": "https://video.twimg.com/amplify_video/2033928805710995456/pl/pglH1pu2pUcpfMmx.m3u8", "aspectRatio": [360, 557], "heightRatio": 154, "type": "video/mp4", "url": "https://video.twimg.com/amplify_video/2033928805710995456/vid/avc1/320x494/NqAoAFwZhRHl4K5r.mp4"}, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/2016950119225036800/W1upvOKl_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Casey Putsch for Ohio Governor", "username": "CaseyPutschOhio"}, "content": "Vivek: \u2018I will shut down your Alma Mater\u2019\n\nReally? The guy who went to Harvard and Yale wants to kill Ohio\u2019s universities?\n\nThese schools ARE Ohio. Just think of all the faculty fired, heartbroken alumni, football Saturdays dead, culture erased. \nAll because a condescending", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 68}}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASGIxqyYz", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 73, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "poopy", "id": 8494879, "raw_content": "Hi everyone,\n\nJust to let those who care know I'm having a double mastectomy this Thursday. I've been quite emotional about all of this but have accepted it is going to be my new normal. This will be my 3rd new normal to adjust to. The first was losing my baby girl at 25 weeks. She was born alive but died shortly after. I was able to become pregnant again not long after and so adjusting to that loss, while very difficult at the time, was nothing compared to the brain aneurysm rupture and 40 days in ICU. I left there with brain damage and had to adjust to a new normal. A normal in which I could no longer do my job, no longer multi task, adjust to memory issues and find new ways to deal with planning and organizing. I made it to the other side and found normal again.\n\nNow I'm losing my breasts. It's ok though bc these breasts have cancer in them and the cancer is trying to kill me. So I'm going to get this done. Look at my new body sometime next week and start accepting this new body minus breasts. It's ok. They accomplished their main purpose when I nursed my girls and they did it well. Now, they have to go. \n\nI've been on a medication break for the last few weeks which has resolved some of the pain and fatigue I was having. I've developed breathing issues as a result of that med and now have to use an inhaler. When I go back on meds it will be something different and hopefully I won't be dealing with the joint pain and extreme fatigue. \n\nI want to thank all of you that have prayed for me and ask for continued prayers as I undertake this new path in life. I'm praying for peace of mind and a return to some measure of my former self where I can be active and enjoy life again. \n\nI'll probably post another update in a few weeks after I've recovered from this surgery just to say I'm alive. \n\nUntil then... ", "author": "ChickNorris", "created": 1773772020577, "profile_picture": "Qe8wSmir2i1S", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "alex_p_keaton_III", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Surgery Thursday ", "last_comment_created": 1773789009734, "content": "<p>Hi everyone,</p>\n<p>Just to let those who care know I'm having a double mastectomy this Thursday. I've been quite emotional about all of this but have accepted it is going to be my new normal. This will be my 3rd new normal to adjust to. The first was losing my baby girl at 25 weeks. She was born alive but died shortly after. I was able to become pregnant again not long after and so adjusting to that loss, while very difficult at the time, was nothing compared to the brain aneurysm rupture and 40 days in ICU. I left there with brain damage and had to adjust to a new normal. A normal in which I could no longer do my job, no longer multi task, adjust to memory issues and find new ways to deal with planning and organizing. I made it to the other side and found normal again.</p>\n<p>Now I'm losing my breasts. It's ok though bc these breasts have cancer in them and the cancer is trying to kill me. So I'm going to get this done. Look at my new body sometime next week and start accepting this new body minus breasts. It's ok. They accomplished their main purpose when I nursed my girls and they did it well. Now, they have to go.</p>\n<p>I've been on a medication break for the last few weeks which has resolved some of the pain and fatigue I was having. I've developed breathing issues as a result of that med and now have to use an inhaler. When I go back on meds it will be something different and hopefully I won't be dealing with the joint pain and extreme fatigue.</p>\n<p>I want to thank all of you that have prayed for me and ask for continued prayers as I undertake this new path in life. I'm praying for peace of mind and a return to some measure of my former self where I can be active and enjoy life again.</p>\n<p>I'll probably post another update in a few weeks after I've recovered from this surgery just to say I'm alive.</p>\n<p>Until then...</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 16, "score_up": 73, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "\ud83d\udca9\u00a0\u00a0POOPY\u00a0\u00a0DAYS", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "2033569655382536258", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASGIyxApA", "is_twitter": true, "is_admin": false, "score": 52, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8495094, "raw_content": "", "author": "raptoris1", "created": 1773778544158, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "toobaditworks", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "twitter.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASGIyxApA.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://twitter.com/SenFettermanPA/status/2033569655382536258", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "John Fetterman: \"I don\u2019t follow the polls. As a Democrat, I unapologetically stand on the side of moral clarity and our ally Israel.\"", "last_comment_created": 1773791996537, "content": "", "score_down": 3, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 13, "score_up": 55, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"twitter": {"quotedTweet": false, "images": [{"width": 1026, "heightRatio": 49, "url": "https://pbs.twimg.com/media/HDiw0ptaAAAyq6T.jpg", "height": 504}], "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 4954, "created": 1773675762000, "id": "2033569655382536258", "video": false, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg